description: Leonardo, Raph and Don investigate the mausoleum that they've set up shop in, searching for signs of intrusion. Leonardo goes off on his own, fearing that Raph and Don's armor isn't stealthy enough. The ninja returns a few minutes later, holding the culprits: two rabbits. Don states that he has to go to Pittsburgh to get some parts. Raphael tells his brothers that he's got to get back to training his Foot Soldiers. Leonardo wants to go along and help out, but Raph refuses the offer, telling Leo that there can only be one person giving orders - and the Foot have chosen Raph. Leo is dejected, but he realizes that Raphael is right. Don offers to take Leo with him to Pittsburgh, but Leo says he doesn't want to sit for that long, so he heads into the sewers to get some exercise as Don flies off in the car. Nearby, we see two men in black suits and sunglasses spying on the Turtles.

Donatello is being questioned by the government authorities that believe the Turtle is an alien (due to his armor and the modified Triceraton aircar). The Feds try to call the Savage Dragon in to identify Don, but the fin-headed cop has gone missing - so some other super heroes from Chicago have come to check out the Turtle via a two-way mirror, but none of them recognize Donny. The man questioning Donatello tells him that he cannot leave until they find someone who can speak on his behalf. When informed of this news, Donatello gets upset and yells at the government agent. Don's actions alarm the heroes who have come to indentify him and they break through the mirror prepared for battle - fortunately, Horridus arrives and she recognizes the ninja before any more violence breaks out.

The Triceraton that teleported aboard the aircar holds a gun to Horridus' head and orders Don to surrender. Donatello complies and is then knocked out of the vehicle by the angry alien. As Don falls, he uses the armor's ability to morph jet engines to save himself - but he doesn't know how to synthesize jet fuel, so he continues his freefall! Fortunately, Don-san is able to morph a helicopter prop that saves him from another deadly fall. Onboard the vehicle, the Triceraton refers to Horridus as "little sister", and the easily influenced hero becomes infatuated with the giant.

name: Reborn To Rage

description:
Nathan Ellstings is a man on the run. He is running from a murder wrap and headed towards demons. Along with Wendy Mckinnes they hunt The Wicked, people who have sold their souls for personal gain. All Wicked can see each other as they truly are, large twisted beasts, while average humans cannot. Nathan can see them by accident of birth and he only stands out to them when he uses his powers. He has the ear of the Pope himself as well many powerful and prominent religious leaders.
 
The pair arrive in a small town and Nathan displays one of his powers, the power of  subtle hypnotic suggestion. The find a young boy has contacted them for help with a possessed young girl.  Carmen wanted to be liked and loved by boys but the Wicked in her slaughtered them instead. The girl transforms into her demon form as Wendy draws a pentagram outside the room to act as a corporal trap for evil. 
 
Nathan uses his psyonic ability to wrestle the girl from inside the demon only for a priest to burst in on Nathan with the naked form of the girl in his arms, he is shredded by the demon who tries to escape but finds the building sealed to it. the Demon grabs a boy but Wendy snatches him back as it gets entrapped in the pentagram and finally destroyed. 
 
In the remains Nathan find an amulet which drags his mind into a vision of his Father being chased by demons and sacrificing himself so that he and his mother can escape. They move around for year avoiding detection until one day The Wicked find and kill his mother.

In New York City a talk-show host and his shock guests are all Wicked parading around on TV pretending to be cheap entertainment when in fact they are helping to corrupt the viewers. 
 
A married priest makes love to his mistress and a spiral mark appeared between his shoulder blades. When he returns home to his wife they also make love only for his lower body to explode spraying the same shape onto the wall in his blood. 
 
Out on the streets Nathan stands next to a legless man playing  a flute. He is a Gatemaster who lost his legs to a shadow demon. the demon that now opens the walls behind him so he can enter Club Wicked, a place for demons, cherubs and evil.

The Fantastic Four as you never could have imagined them! The trusted advisor at Magneto's right hand is almost certainly the second most powerful man in the world. But the question is...will second-best be enough for Victor Von Doom?
name: A Doctor in the House

description: Victor Von Doom has everything he could possibly want…love, power, and the position formerly occupied by his dead rival, Reed Richards. But would he be willing to throw all these things away just for a chance at the only thing he really wants—the throne of the House of M?
name: Four The Hard Way

description: The treacherous Victor Von Doom's fantastic, fearsome foursome have at last maneuvered Magneto into the one place he is vulnerable, and it is time for Doom to strike. But, for all his elaborate planning, is there anything-or anyone-Doom has overlooked? And how much will that oversight cost him? Don't miss the exciting, action-packed finale!
name: King For A Day

description:
Guy Gardner is in trouble. The Palindrordnilapians have sent three aliens by the names of Buk-50, Boom and Thoom to take guy down and his new ring is all out of power. Guy however is able to put up a good fight even without super-powers. He even flattens the trio with a bus and later a subway train.

Meanwhile Kilowog is looking for Guy. He has been sent by the guardians to get Sinestro's old ring back. He even checks in on Booster Gold ans Blue Beetle at the Justice League America headquarters. Once he finds Guy he lets him keep his ring because he deems it powerless. No sooner does Kilowog leave and Guy's ring inexplicably regains power. As soon as this happens Guy takes care of the three Aliens and is immediately transported to the Palindrordnilapian ship. The Palindrordnilapians offer Guy guy a job as leader of their security firm for outer space travel. Guy explains that he want to test his ring to find out why it's malfunctioning before he agrees. So the Palindrordnilapians agree to round up some super tough aliens to test Guy out.
name: What's a Guy to Do?

description: Prior to this issue Guy Gardner started having problems with his yellow ring. In this issue it shows him beating on a big red alien. This is done for the whole issue. After he beats him up he looks at a long line of big ugly aliens in a line that seems to go off into the horizon. Then Guy says the only word in the whole issue. "Next." More is said on the cover than in the whole book.
name: In Space, No One Can Hear You Fight!

description:
Spoiler Alert

The Golden Boy Guy Gardner is out on the town top hat and all, celebrating his new successful career with the Gardners of the Universe. The Palindrordnilaps have given Guy a lot of money to be the leader of an interstellar security business. As he celebrates his success he gets hit in the back of his head by a bullet. Luckily for Guy he had his power ring protecting him. Guy's new ring he took from Sinestro protected him from the gold jacketed bullet. As it turned out a henchmen of Goldface sent him to kill Guy. As Guy is about to trounce the henchman, Ice shows up and and saves the henchman from getting spattered. It turns out Ice has been keeping an eye on Guy and showed because she's worried about him, and wanted to talk.

All Guy has to say is too little too late. He also decides he is going to do the one thing Hal Jordan has never done and thats get Goldface. This is much better than his original plan of just beating Hal Jordan up. With this decision Guy travels to see Kari Limbo and have her tell him were to find Goldface.
name: Golden Boy

description:
Hal Jordon has finally caught up to Guy Gardner and his new yellow power ring, and it turns out that the two heroes are both trying to catch Goldface.

Hal suggests the two team up but Guy doesn’t want to be shown up, so instead Guy beats up Hal. Their fight is stopped when Guy’s current girl Sally and Hal’s best friend Tom are in danger. The two heroes save their friends but Guy still doesn’t want Hal’s help, so Hall takes Tom and flies off to San Francisco. Guy and Sally fly to McTeague’s Corner in Death Valley, the location that Mr. Gullet, Goldface’s lackey, gave them as Goldface’s hideout.

When Guy and Sally get to McTeague’s Corner, Goldface had already been alerted, and had setup some traps. One trap involved some aliens, one of which is a able to steal Guy’s ring and anther that is able to sneak up on Sally.

Meanwhile in San Francisco, Hal and Tom have found out some secret of where Goldface is truly hiding.
name: Two for the Seesaw
Yesterday's Sins 1 of 4: Back in the Days
Yesterday's Sins 2 of 4: Dream a Deadly Dream

description: To escape from physical torture, Guy retreats into memories of a fractured childhood.
name: Yesterday's Sins 3 of 4: Inside Out / Outside In
Yesterday's Sins 4 of 4: Guys And Draals

description:
Guy relives the death of his father as he mounts an escape for himself and the imprisoned Green Lanterns before heading back to Earth to confront his doppelgänger.

A clone of Guy Gardner is made by the Draal. This clone runs amok and even kill a villain named Blake. The Justice League and the real guy have to bring him in.

Continued from Justice League America #83 - The Trouble With Guys
name: The trouble With Guys Part II

description: Guy Gardner is propelled in a new direction when he's forced to fight a foe he can't possibly defeat-his own brother, who he's long thought dead, and who has become the ruthless assassin, Militia.
name: Total Warfare

description: Guy Gardner's battle with the armored killing machine Militia-secretly Guy's own brother, Mace-reaches a shattering conclusion that inspires Gardner to assume his new superhero name, Warrior.

Warrior's ring overloads and becomes useless following the events in Green Lantern (1990) #50. Now, to stop Militia, Warrior must enlist Blue Beetle's aid in building a suit of battle armor.

Needing powers, Guy goes to his technological genius friend the Blue Beetle for a suit of armor.
name: Emerald Fallout, Part One

description: When his power ring overloads, Warrior has to don battle armor to take down Militia. Plus, Warrior continues to experience the dire ramifications of “Emerald Twilight,” leading to Militia's final downfall!
name: Emerald Fallout, Part Two

description: With the aid of Golden Age Green Lantern Alan Scott, Warrior assembles a team to investigate what's happened on the planet Oa. Alongside Martian Manhunter, the Ray, Wonder Woman, Darkstar Ferrin Colos, Captain Atom and Arisia, Warrior battles rogue Green Lantern Hal Jordan as the assembled heroes fight to take down one of their own.
name: Emerald Fallout, Part Three

description: It's Warrior versus Hal Jordan in an all-splash-page issue for a planet-shattering battle that Guy Gardner can't possibly win!
name: Emerald Fallout, Part Four

description:
Warrior begins his quest for new superpowers after the destruction of his ring. It's cliffhanger after cliffhanger as Warrior is joined by new character Buck Wargo, a man every bit as hard-edged as Guy Gardner. But before Warrior can do anything, he has to escape the coma world of the demonic Dementor.

Guy and his friends quest deep into the jungle to search for a source of super-powers. Unfortunately they are hit by many problems, dinosaurs, Nazis and a traitor in their ranks.
name: Road of Terror

description:
Finally, Warrior's quest for new powers ends…but so does his life as he knows it. A major turning point for Guy Gardner.

Beast-people, double-crosses and Nazis on dinosaurs. These are just a few of Guy's problems as he tried to gain superpowers.
name: Wet Dreams

description: A Zero Hour crossover issue. As Zero Hour rages, Guy Gardner, Steel, Supergirl, and the alternate-timeline Batgirl follow Extant across multiple eras. In prehistoric time, the quartet is joined by Anthro and Java against Extant. In the Wild West, they are joined by the full host of DC’s western heroes. Guy Gardner uses his newfound ability to morph weapons from his skin to help push the advantage. Time continues to break down, and the quartet picks up Lady Blackhawk as they jump to an era in Guy’s past. They meet Kari Limbo, and try to save Hal Jordan from becoming Parallax, but fail before being pulled to Coast City the day it was destroyed. Guy finds out that Kari was on the scene, and tries to save her. However, as Guy tries, Coast City is destroyed, and Guy is sucked back into the time portal as the world fades to white.
name: Killing Time!

description: In this extra-sized 25th issue, Warrior—with the aid of the Phantom Stranger—plunges into a nightmarish world where he battles the diabolical Dementor for the life of his estranged brother. During the course of the struggle, Guy Gardner discovers the truth behind his uncontrollable rages...and fears he could become as dangerous as the villain he fights. Plus, Warrior learns about the death of his former love Ice and faces a different kind of battle—this time with his grief.
name: Family Ties

description:
Warrior tests his new powers against the ultimate terrorist, the Black Serpent, a modern-day pirate who holds the president hostage in New York's World Trade Center. Warrior's battle against the villain and his “Wilders” becomes explosive as Guy Gardner's new powers prove to be a threat to the city as dangerous as the terrorists.

The President of the United States is endangered when a modern-day pirate crew attacks the skyscraper he is visiting.
name: Snakebit!

description:
Part one of the three-part story, “Capital Punishment,” guest-starring Steel. Guy Gardner teams with John Henry Irons when Warrior arrives in Washington, D.C., to rescue his brother from the Quorum. But the Quorum has activated Sledge, a super-soldier from the past with orders to kill. Plus, Superman makes a cameo appearance.

Under D.C. sleeps the monstrous being known as Sledge. Until now. Sledge is defeated when the Washington Monument falls on his head.
name: Capital Punishment: Act 1 - Wake-Up Call

description: Warrior goes berserk when he learns that Major Force may have been responsible for his mother's death. Even if Guy Gardner lets the villain live, Green Lantern Kyle Rayner has his own vendetta with Major Force!
name: Capital Punishment: Act 2 - Deck the Hood With Blows of Folly

description:
You're invited to the grand opening of Warriors, Guy Gardner's new bar—a tavern exclusive to metahumans…and quite possibly the most dangerous place in the DC Universe! On opening night, a huge turnout gets the festivities into full swing. But the bash quickly degenerates into an all-star free-for-all of raucous excitement, and it's a safe bet Gardner will be calling the contractors to fix the place in the morning— especially after Lobo crashes the party…literally!

Guy Gardner hosts a party at his Warrior Bar. It seems like everyone in the DCU shows up even John Constantine who at this point was at residence at the Vertigo imprint. This is a grand opening like no other in comic books.

Real people cameo of Arnold Schwarzenegger, Sylvester Stallone and Bruce Willis on Page 22.

This comic would also have two covers, the fold-out and the side profile normal stock.

Note: The alternate cover is a homage to Edward Hoppers Nighthawks
name: It's My Party and I'll Fight if I Want To

description: Superman and Supergirl guest-star in a story continued from ACTION COMICS (1938 DC) #709. Warrior goes berserk as his incredible powers go completely out of control.
name: The Enemy of My Friend

description: Guest stars Supergirl and Sentinel (Alan Scott) battle Dementor when the villain arrives to claim the berserk Warrior, only to fall prey to their worst nightmare.
name: Channel Surfin' A Nightmare

description: The Justice League guest-stars in part one of the seven-part crossover story “The Way of the Warrior.” It's Warrior versus the JLA when Guy Gardner confronts his old teammates about the death of Ice. But a greater danger looms in the form of unstoppable alien killing machines, the Kraggz! Continues in JUSTICE LEAGUE AMERICA (1987) #101.
name: The Way of the Warrior - Part 1: Give Me A Space to Call My Own

description: Guy Gardner and the Justice League head into Tormock space.
name: The Way of the Warrior - Part 4: Into the Valley of Death

description: Part 7 of the 7-part crossover story “The Way of the Warrior,” continued from HAWKMAN (1993 3rd Series) #23. It's the ultraviolent, take-no-prisoners conclusion! Lobo joins Warrior, Diana, Hawkman and the Bad One for a bloody showdown with the galaxy's deadliest assassins!
name: The Way of the Warrior - Part 7: Deathrock: Justice is Coming!

description:
Tagline: CORPS BREACH!

Guy uses his new-found powers to rescue several long lost Green Lanterns and one abused Darkstar.
name: Falling Down

description: Guy's evil clone decides to go on a murderous rampage though the Warrior's bar. Save the Scotch!
name: The Darker Side of Evil
Seduction of the Not So Innocent

description: Guy's mother moves into Warrior's, causing chaos in her wake.
name: Good Things Ain't Been Comin' in the Packages I've Been Gettin'!

description: A real-life adventure mirrors the plot of a proposed Guy television show.
name: Guys & Babes in Toyland

description: Dementor has taken a fashion show hostage; already there is a bodycount. Gardner swoops in for the save but is having trouble because he is now a she.
name: A Gender Bender In The Blender

description: Guy's enemies gather to kill him. He fights back and many die...unfortunately a dear friend falls dead as well.
name: A Warrior's Passing Part 1 You Broke My Heart... So I Busted Your Jaw

description: Most of Guy's enemies are downed or dead. Unfortunately Major Force has slain Guy's friend Arisa. Now it's time for a face off between them both down at the docks.
name: A Warrior's Passing Part 2 The Last Stand

description:
Compiles the following stories:

  • Once Upon A Time...
  • Hypersensitive: A Changer for all Reasons
  • See My Finger.  See My Thumb.  See My Fist?  You Better Run!
  • The Gardner Gals in... Dateless in a One Gender Town
What is real? As Bloodshot continues his search to piece together his life, he only has one trail to follow, and all things lead to Angelo Mortalli.
name: Dead Man Walking

description: Bloodshot's journey leads him back to where it all began, and where his old life ended, Project Lazarus. Dr. Stroheim may be the only one to provide Bloodshot with the answers he seeks, but will their confrontation only lead to even more questions?
name: The postmodern Prometheus

description: Bloodshot comes face-to-face with the truth of his past and original identity. Does he have what it takes to face his demons? Or, for that matter, are those demons even real?
name: Panopticon

description: After his encounter with Simon Oreck, Bloodshot takes a voyage into his own mind to recover what he has left of his original self. As devastating as some of what he comes across may be, does our hero have what it takes to "re-discover" himself?
name: The Society Of The Mind

description: Bloodshot breaks into D.O.A.'s headquarters only to encounter, who else, but X-O Manowar! What will happen when these two super-powered beings face off?
name: Hot Metal, Part 1

description: With his nanites causing all sorts of trouble for X-O Manowar, Bloodshot takes control of the fight. As he tears his way to the man inside of the armor, Bloodshot discovers more about the man he is himself.
name: Hot Metal, Part 2

description: In the aftermath of his battle with X-O Manowar, Bloodshot discovers the truth behind his former identity. Once he realizes how terrible of a person he used to be, however, he takes matters into his own hands quite literally by trying to take his own life.
name: The Smoking Gun

description:
Bloodshot takes a trip to the infamous Area 51. As the man he used to be, Raymond Garrison, was part of the team that planned the security of the site, he should have no trouble getting in. Whether or not he can handle what awaits him inside is a whole other question though...

Back in the present, Bloodshot journeys to Nevada's infamous "Area 51," the rumored U.S. government installation of stored UFO technology. He learns that there's a cover-up going on, all right, one that Raymond Garrison was once in on. And what is the connection between D.O.A., the covert organization known as Blackworks, and the aliens who have recently menaced X-O Manowar?
name: Dreamland

description: Continuing to backtrack the steps of his former life, Bloodshot finds his way to Vietnam. After eluding a P.R.S. agent, Bloodshot finds himself facing off with the deadly assassin, Warcat!
name: Apocalypse Now And Then

description: It's the Fight of the Living Dead! Turns out that Warcat wasn't the only enemy that Bloodshot had to worry about. In fact, the horde of undead Viet Cong sprouting up in the wilderness might just be more of a threat, all things considered. Luckily Shadowman is there to lend a hand.
name: The Quick And The Dead

description: On the hunt to learn more about the man he once was deep in the heart of Russia, an encounter with Soviet psychotronic experiments shows Bloodshot truths he was never prepared for!
name: Unanticipated Psychotronic Singularities And Fragmentation Of The Explicate Order Within A Severely Distorted Finited N-Dimensional Manifold

description: Bloodshot's hunt for the truth takes him all the way to Vatican City. Hidden there deep in the forbidden libraries he'll get a glimpse of the secret rewritten history of himself and his whole universe.
name: Uncorrected Proof

description: With all the pieces of the truth about himself falling into place Bloodshot returns to D.O.A. to confront Simon Oreck. But before the final reackoning he'll need to survive the ravenous hungers of his own twisted clone.
name: Final Jeopardy

description: Bloodshot's mission has come to an end, permanently, and seemingly at his own hand. What fate awaits him in death... and beyond? The truth of Project Lazarus and the Bloodshot's creation finally revealed in this startling final issue!
name: Epilogue

description: Raymond Garrison is only sure about one thing: that he is not Raymond Garrison. Having survived death, with no recollections, his mind, body and soul have been remade. A mysterious organization, Project Lazarus, has formatted his body with nanite enhancements that grant him superhuman abilities, but also leave him more machine than man, and more monster than human. After escaping his captors, Bloodshot now searches for answers as to who he is, destroying anything that attempts to stop him.
name: Behold, A Pale Horseman

volume.name: Antiquities War on the World of Magic the Gathering
Antiquities War on the World of Magic the Gathering
